727746f-b.text:
Qlueens Boulevard, at the S. W. corner of 57th Avenue, showing the Samuel Reime House, a pre-Revolutionary house. It was also known as the Arnold's House. One Bretonier was the owner in 1852. The house was altered in 1865. Eugene L. Armbruster is authority
for the above data.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  Views 1,2: Oct., 1928

727748f-b.text:
Queens Boulevard, west from Fifty-seventh Avenue, showing an area of OQueens Boulevard prior to its widening. View No. 1 shows in the foreground No. 58 (old No.) Queens Boulevard at the S.W. corner of above Boulevard and Fifty-sixth Avenue. It was the property of one Arnoldi prior to 1873. Also seen in this view is the steeple of the new First Presbyterian Church of Newtown. Its steeple has since been rem;oved. View No. 2 shows the north side of the Boulevard. The extension of Mrs. Raymond's house at the right foreground is west of Fiftysixth ..venue. (Laconia Street also known as Horsebrook Road). View. No. 3 shows the hhouse alone prior to its removal. View Ho. 2 also shows the old First Presbyterian Church in the background. View No. 4 shows the house according to E.L. Arbruster to now, 1925, be on the north (west) side of Fifty-seventh Avenue (Caldwell Avenue) about 50 feet west (south) of Van Horn Street. However it does not appear in
the 1929 Atlas of Queens County.
April 1923.
View 2: August 1924.
View 3: February , 1924.
View 4: July 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
